fields.name: Royal County Down (Championship)
fields.description: Royal County Down is located in one of the world's most naturally beautiful links settings in the Murlough Nature Reserve. Against the magnificent backdrop of the Mountains of Mourne, the links stretches along the shores of Dundrum Bay, zigzagging back and forth to provide a different vista from virtually every hole.
fields.video_description: The 2007 Walker Cup was a mismatch on paper but turned out to be one of the best matches in event history.
fields.pro_golfer_1_review: "Going by what Rory has been telling me, it could possibly be the best course I play this year" - Sergio Garcia
fields.pro_golfer_2_review: "Great morning golf at Royal County Down. I'm biased but definitely one of the top few courses in the world!" - Rory McIlroy

fields.name: St Andrews Old Course
fields.description: St Andrews is regarded as the "Home of Golf". The Old Course, believed to be the oldest golf course in the world, dates back more than 600 years. The oldest and most iconic golf course in the world. The Swilcan Bridge and Hell Bunker are recognised across the globe, yet the greatest feature of the Old Course is that despite its grand status it remains a public golf course, open to all.
fields.video_description: Ross Fisher shot a 61 in the final round of the 2017 Alfred Dunhill Links Championship, breaking the Old Course record at St. Andrews.
fields.pro_golfer_1_review: “I could take out of my life everything except my experiences at St Andrews and I would still have a rich, full life.” - Bobby Jones
fields.pro_golfer_2_review: “It may be years before I fully appreciate it, but I am inclined to believe that winning The Open at the Home of Golf is the ultimate achievement in the sport.” - Tiger Woods

fields.name: Trump Turnberry (Ailsa)
fields.description: Trump Turnberry is a world renowned bucket list golf destination. Home to the Ailsa course, host of four Open Championships, which is a 7,489 yard, par-71. The Ailsa course is known for its tough opening holes and is demanding for even the most skilled golfers.
fields.video_description: Recap of Tom Watson's battle with Stewart Cink in the Final Round of the 2009 Open Championship
fields.pro_golfer_1_review: "The thrill of competing is tremendous, and the vibes I felt from those people and my peers during the week at Turnberry will never go away." - Tom Watson
fields.pro_golfer_2_review: "Winning the Open here in 2009 doesn't get much better" - Stewart Cink

fields.name: Sunningdale Golf Club
fields.description: Sunningdale’s Old Course was designed by twice winner of The Open Championship, Willie Park Junior and opened in 1901. The land on which it was constructed belonged to St. John’s College, Cambridge and mainly consisted of heather, gorse and pine trees.
fields.video_description: A golf day at Sunningdale with celebrities
fields.pro_golfer_1_review: “Some of the American players have not had chance to play courses like Sunningdale before, and I tell them it is how golf should be. It is unique and it brings out the child in you”. - Tom Watson
fields.pro_golfer_2_review: Greg Norman was a big fan of Sunningdale Golf Club

fields.name: Royal Portrush (Dunlace)
fields.description: Legendary, long-standing 18-hole golf course with scenic views, a dress code & a clubhouse. The Dunlace is one of the courses on the rota of the Open Championship and last hosted the tournament in 2019.
fields.video_description: The 148th Open Round 4 Highlights from Royal Portrush
